node.title: South Australia records 18 new COVID-19 cases, 16 connected to school reunion cluster
node.description: South Australia records 18 new cases of COVID-19, with 16 of those connected to a high school reunion held in Adelaide's eastern suburbs over the weekend.

node.title: Grieving parents describe 'horrendous' response from Veterans' Affairs Department to request for their son's medical records
node.description: A grieving mother's request for access to her soldier son's medical records has never been granted by the Veterans' Affairs Department, despite his 2016 suicide being linked to his Afghanistan service, the veteran's suicide inquiry is told.

node.title: Education Minister Alan Tudge stood aside amid abuse allegations, PM tells parliament
node.description: The Prime Minister tells parliament that Education Minister Alan Tudge has stood aside after a former Liberal staffer made fresh claims against him, alleging she was in an emotionally, and on one occasion, physically abusive relationship with him.

node.title: South Island councils split on requiring Covid-19 vaccine pass
node.description: Most of the large east coast ones are requiring a vaccine pass to enter libraries, pools and museums, but none of the three West Coast councils will be using them.

node.title: Investigator in Wisconsin 2020 election review tried to overturn Biden win
node.description: Ron Heuer, one of the investigators in the election review ordered by the GOP-led Wisconsin Assembly, was involved in two failed lawsuits to overturn Biden's 2020 victory.

node.title: Backing Ilhan Omar, Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez Says Boebert Part of 'Ku Klux Klan Caucus'
node.description: Two recent videos have shown Boebert referring to the Muslim Congress member as a terrorist bomber and a member of the "Jihad Squad."

node.title: Hospitals Among Tennessee Entities Banned from Asking Workers for COVID Vaccine Proof
node.description: Jason Mumpower said his office "can no longer find that compliance" with the state law "would result in a loss of federal funding," thus halting exemptions.

node.title: Man Who Threatened Congressmembers If They Didn't Support Trump Sentenced to Nearly 3 Years
node.description: Ryder Winegar was accused of threatening to hang lawmakers if they wouldn't "get behind Donald Trump" in phone messages left on the morning of Dec. 16, 2020.

node.title: As First Case of Omicron Variant Hits U.S., Transit Mask Mandates to Be Extended
node.description: The infected individual returned to the U.S. from South Africa on November 22. They tested positive for the Omicron variant seven days later.

node.title: Amid Spills And Ambition For Renewable Energy, California Reconsiders Oil Pipeline
node.description: The proposal represents California's dilemma of meeting present energy production needs while also wanting to commit to progressive renewable energy policies.

node.title: Belfast collective wins prestigious Turner Prize with recreation of illegal pub
node.description: An 11-person Belfast collective aiming to transcend Northern Ireland's political and religious divides wins the $46,750 Turner Prize with a recreation of a traditional Irish illicit pub.

node.title: US police officer fired after fatally shooting man in wheelchair
node.description: Bodycam footage captures the moment an off-duty officer opens fire on a man in a motorised wheelchair who allegedly stole a toolbox from a supermarket.

node.title: Pubgoers trapped for days with only each other and an Oasis cover band for company
node.description: Concertgoers find themselves snowed in at a 17th century British pub, after seeing an Oasis cover band.

node.title: Woman, 19, pleads not guilty to 'headphones' murder of 16yo boy
node.description: Kayla Dawson pleads not guilty to killing shoolboy Jason Galleghan during an August party at her home in Sydney after an alleged dispute over a pair of headphones.

node.title: NSW health authorities 'concerned' about new Omicron COVID-19 case
node.description: Health authorities in NSW confirm a seventh Omicron COVID-19 variant in the state, this time from someone who has not been in southern Africa.

node.title: Michigan school shooting: Student kills three and wounds eight
node.description: A 15-year-old has killed three fellow students and injured eight others, including a teacher, in a high school shooting in the US state of Michigan.

node.title: 'It's awesome': Kaikōura locals ready to dive for pāua after 5 years
node.description: Five years after the earthquake which devastated seabeds along the Kaikōura coastline, people are once again able to gather pāua from its shores.

node.title: One in three employees high risk for burnout during pandemic
node.description: Workplace burnout is soaring as workers find it harder to balance their work life with pressures from the Covid-19 pandemic.

node.title: January 6 committee recommends contempt for former DOJ official
node.description: The panel voted unanimously to recommend that the House find Jeffrey Clark in contempt of Congress.

node.title: Music legend Clarence Avant's wife shot and killed in Beverly Hills home
node.description: The 81-year-old, known for her philanthropy work in the Los Angeles area, died early Wednesday morning.

node.title: Here are all the charges against the suspect in the Oxford High School shooting.
node.description: The 15-year-old suspect faces 24 felony counts, including terrorism causing death.

node.title: Possible Contempt Charge Hangs Over Trump Justice Dept. Official
node.description: The House committee investigating the Capitol riot agreed to delay action against Jeffrey Clark until after he could be interviewed again.

node.title: Suspect in Michigan School Shooting Faces Murder and Terrorism Charges
node.description: A 15-year-old accused of killing four of his classmates and wounding seven other people had described wanting to attack the school in cellphone videos and a journal, the authorities said.

node.title: $71.5M Compensation Fund Announced for Women Abused By Doctor, Including Andrew Yang's Wife
node.description: The settlement was agreed to by 79 women who accused former gynecologist Robert Hadden, and the two hospitals where he worked, of partaking in abuse.

node.title: Suspect in Deadly Waukesha Parade Crash Says in Interview He Feels 'Demonized' in Jail
node.description: "I just feel like I'm being monster – demonized," the suspect said.

node.title: Catholic Church Cancels YAF-Sponsored Anti-Abortion Talk by Matt Walsh as Faculty Protest
node.description: The Young America's Foundation found a new venue for Walsh's appearance after St. Francis Xavier College Church cancelled the event.

node.title: Biden Scoffs When Asked if He Thinks Trump Put Him at Risk of COVID at Presidential Debate
node.description: Three days after his first debate against Biden, Trump announced on Twitter that he and his wife had tested positive for coronavirus.

node.title: Families of Astrowold crush turn down Travis Scott's offer to pay for funerals
node.description: Attorneys for the families of four of the victims of the Astroworld Festival crush say they have received a letter from performer Travis Scott's attorney, Daniel Petrocelli, in which an offer was made to pay for the funerals of their lost loved ones.

node.title: Meet the nearby black holes that are set to collide and create a 'monster'
node.description: Astronomers have discovered a pair of supermassive black holes that are the closest to Earth ever observed – and they're on a collision course with each other.

node.title: Alex Carey confirmed as Australian wicketkeeper for first two Ashes Tests
node.description: South Australia's Alex Carey will be Australia's wicketkeeper for at least the first two Ashes Tests, after he is added to the squad in place of former skipper Tim Paine.
